(60, 'com_content.article', 'Swati', 'swati', '<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Swati is the fifteenth nakshatra among the <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=category&amp;id=12&amp;Itemid=112">27 Nakshatras</a> studied in Vedic Astrology. Swati is ruled by <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=8:rahu&amp;catid=9:9-planets&amp;Itemid=109">Rahu</a> and the presiding deity is Vayu. All the 4 Padas are located in Tula rashi and the gana for swati is devta. Though Tula rashi is the rashi of balance, Rahu creates imbalance and unrest in the lives of Swati natives. Unless <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=7:shani&amp;catid=9:9-planets&amp;Itemid=109">Shani</a> is involved the inner feelings and outer behavior of Swati natives tends to be poles apart.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Physical Features: Natives both males and females are attractive and alluring. Females have a distinguished speech and manner of walking.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Character &amp; Events: Swati natives have mysterious behavior. The outward calm and composed demeanor due to Tula Rashi''s balanced persona is hindered by the inner turmoil and uneasy feelings brought forth by Rahu who always wants more. Swati natives cannot stay at one place and like to travel as and when they please. While Rahu encourages taboo breaking activities which are anti-social and unlawful the balancing view of Tula rarely allows that side to be in public view. They may be enticed to pursue taboo activities in secret but outwardly they love to show simplicity and good mannerisms. Generally Swati females have a truthful and straight forward character. While males are thoughtful and slow in their actions they are brilliant at analyzing work based on intelligence and logic. Swati males are religious and somewhat orthodox. Swati natives are peace loving but prone to be hot tempered and revengeful when instigated. They are adamant in their views and independent in their approach. They do not level criticism at others and cannot handle criticism leveled at them. Period after 30 years sees growth in business and professional sector. Swati natives have ideal career in travelling sector, pharmacist, diplomats, gold smith and politicians (if Shani is involved).</p>\r\n<p>Family Life: Swati natives do not have an ideal married life. While the outer picture is a happy married life the inner reality is different. Native may have no stability in matters of money and place of accommodation.</p>\r\n<p>Health: Mysterious conditions possible due to Swati being a nakshatra of Rahu.</p>\r\n<p>Positives: Business Minded, Friendly, Independent.</p>\r\n<p>Negatives: Hot Temper</p>\r\n<p>Remedies: Swati natives should pray to Saraswati and Bhairav (Avatar of Rudra). &nbsp;</p>', 1, '', 0, 1, '{"show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_layout":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 0, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 899, '', '2014-02-02 02:30:30', 899, '2014-03-06 11:56:08', '*', '2014-02-02 02:30:30', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 48, 175, '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', 0, 5, 12, 'swati nakshatra, 27 nakshatra, nakshatra ruled by rahu', 'swati nakshatra in vedic astrology', 13, '', 1),
(61, 'com_content.article', 'Vishakha', 'vishakha', '<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Vishakha Nakshatra is the sixteenth nakshatra among <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=category&amp;id=12&amp;Itemid=112">27 Nakshatras</a> in Vedic Astrology. While the first 3 Padas are located in <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=28:tula&amp;catid=11:12-signs&amp;Itemid=111">Tula Rashi</a> the last pada of Vishakha is in <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=29:vrischika&amp;catid=11:12-signs&amp;Itemid=111">Vrischika Rashi</a>. The presiding diety for Vishakha are Indra and Agni while the gana is Rakhshasa. The ruling planet is the benevolent <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=5:guru&amp;catid=9:9-planets&amp;Itemid=109">Guru</a>. Vishakha is also called Anuradha which is the birth star of <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=1:surya&amp;catid=9:9-planets&amp;Itemid=109">Surya</a> while it is also called Radha who is known as the consort of Lord Krishna. Vishakha has the nature of its deities Indra and Agni which is full of splendor and vigor albeit for a short period of time.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Physical Features: Vishakha natives are round, bright and physical appearance is attractive. Some natives are obese and tall while others have a short and lean structure. Vishaksha females have delicate features and a soft and pleasing voice but underneath the delicacy likes a very strong character.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Character &amp; Events: Vishakha natives are full of vigor and vitality and possess intelligence of the highest order. They are firm believers in God but do not believe in orthodox principles or age old traditions. They are fond of adopting modern ideas. They treat all religion, caste and creed as equal. Vishakha natives are also impatient, aggressive and quite quarrelsome. They are quite active but not so much popular. Their aggressive behavior is disliked by others. Also they have lot of pride and are easily offended. They may have enemies due to hot temper and arrogant nature. Natives born in Tula rashi in the first 3 Padas have strong diplomatic skills. Natives sometimes are spendthrift while other times they are stingy in spending. Vishakha natives are best advised to do independent business or high responsibility jobs. Career as Psychologist, Medical Diagnosis, Counseling, Investigative Journalism and Scientific Research is best suited. Due to good oratary skill natives could also be good Politicians.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Family Life: Vishakha females are quite appealing to opposite sex and generally have a fortunate marriage. Husband is good natured and wealthy. Female natives are likely to have very few children. Female natives are fond of travels and travel often with their partners. Vishakha natives have more enemies as compared to friends. Vishakha natives do not get appropriate love or care from mother owing to death of mother or other unforseen circumstances. Although they respect their father very much and father also is the more doting of the two parents there are bound to be differences with father. This makes the natives hard working and self made individuals since childhood. Although they love their partners they are prone to addictions or extra-marital affairs. These traits cause problems in family and social life.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Health: Health remains normally good but natives are prone to paralytic attack especially after 55 years of age. Ashthma is also observed among natives.</p>\r\n<p>Positives: Intelligent, Spiritual, Good Communicator.</p>\r\n<p>Negatives: Quarrelsome, Restless and Aggressive.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Remdies: Praying to Lord Krishna and Lord Shiva</p>', 1, '', 0, 1, '{"show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_layout":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 0, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 899, '', '2014-02-02 02:31:14', 899, '2014-03-06 11:59:41', '*', '2014-02-02 02:31:14', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 49, 177, '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', 0, 4, 11, 'vishakha nakshatra, nakshatra ruled by guru, 27 nakshatra, nakshatra ruled by jupiter', 'vishakha nakshatra in vedic astrology', 13, '', 1),
(62, 'com_content.article', 'Anuradha', 'anuradha', '<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Anuradha is the seventeenth nakshatra among the <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=category&amp;id=12&amp;Itemid=112">27 nakshatras</a> in Vedic Astrology. All the 4 Padas of Anuradha are in <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=29:vrischika&amp;catid=11:12-signs&amp;Itemid=111">Vrischika Rashi</a> and the presiding diety is Mitra who is one of the 12 Adityas. Symbol for Anuradha is a lotus flower and the gana is devta. Anuradha is ruled by <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=7:shani&amp;catid=9:9-planets&amp;Itemid=109">Shani</a> and located in Vrischika Rashi which is ruled by <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=3:mangal&amp;catid=9:9-planets&amp;Itemid=109">Mangal</a>. Shani and Mangal are polar opposites in terms of personality. Natives with <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=2:chandra&amp;catid=9:9-planets&amp;Itemid=109">Chandra</a> in Anuradha take time to learn to balance between the negativity of Shani and impatience of Mangal. Slowly they learn the art to apply Shani''s hard work and discipline to Mangal''s vigor and afterwards success follows.</p>\r\n<p>Physical Features: Anuradha natives have a beautiful face and bright eyes. They have somewhat of a dejected look on their face due to the inner termoil of Shani-Mangal fight to dominate individuals personality. They are generally lean and tall.</p>\r\n<p>Character &amp; Events: Female natives are clever, witty and fun loving. They are surrounded by admiring circle of friends. Often they invite envy and malice from others who are jelous of them. Males are robust and healthy but derive very little enjoyment in life. While their speech shows warmth and kindness their inner heart is filled with malice. Due to their revengeful character there is no inner peace possible. Natives both male and females face several difficulties in life but can successfully overcome those obstacles. Natives are fim believer in God. These natives spend an independent life and start working at a very young age of 17 or 18. Life between 17 to 48 would be full of trials with some occassional benefits. But life after 48 years would be extremely good. Natives are best suited to pursue business but if employed they would get on quite well with superiors. Career in conflict resolutions, deal makers and negotiators would give maximum benefits.</p>\r\n<p>Family Life: Natives have strained relationship with parents and siblings. They live an independent life and generally settle abroad. Marital life is happy and a good partner is indicated. Children are successful if the native provides proper attention, care, love and affection to the children. Female natives are devoted to their partners and observe religious paractices sternly. She is generally devoted to in-laws and this trait gives her good rewards.</p>\r\n<p>Health: Natives are prone to cough and cold.</p>\r\n<p>Positive: Deal Maker. Friendly Appearance.</p>\r\n<p>Negatives: Revengeful, No Inner Peace</p>\r\n<p>Remedies: Anuradha natives should worship the 12 Adityas and chant the Gayatri Mantra.&nbsp;</p>', 1, '', 0, 1, '{"show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_layout":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 0, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 899, '', '2014-02-02 02:32:08', 899, '2014-03-06 12:02:20', '*', '2014-02-02 02:32:08', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 50, 179, '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', 0, 3, 10, 'anuradha nakshatra, 27 nakshatra, nakshtra ruled by shani, nakshatra ruled by saturn', 'anuradha nakshatra in vedic astrology', 13, '', 1),
(63, 'com_content.article', 'Jyestha', 'jytestha', '<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Jyestha is the eighteenth nakshatra among the <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=category&amp;id=12&amp;Itemid=112">27 Nakshatras</a> in Vedic Astrology. All the 4 Padas of Jyestha are in <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=29:vrischika&amp;catid=11:12-signs&amp;Itemid=111">Vrischika Rashi</a> while the presiding diety is Indra. The ruling planet is <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=4:buddh&amp;catid=9:9-planets&amp;Itemid=109">Budh</a> and gana is Rakshasha. Symbol is an earring resembling Vishnu''s Sudrashan Chakra. Jyestha comes under the category of Gandmoola Nakshatra. Jyestha means the Eldest or Best in the family.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Physical Features: Natives have good physical stamina and attractive figure but teeth maybe defective.</p>\r\n<p>Character &amp; Events: Jyestha is located in Vrischika Rashi which is ruled by <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=3:mangal&amp;catid=9:9-planets&amp;Itemid=109">Mangala</a> and nakshatra itself is ruled by <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=4:buddh&amp;catid=9:9-planets&amp;Itemid=109">Budh</a>. Hence due to the Mangal-Budh relationship the natives are dependent but at the same time bound to be critical in speech. Jyestha natives thrive on being the main souce of financial income and social stability for the family. They understand the importance of time and are quite loyal to their responsibilities. They learn to adapt quickly to difficult situations. They are often restless and bound to make a mountain of a small mole. Natives are hot tempered and prone to stain good relationships. They generally occupy an influential position and command respect among others. They can rise to top ranks through their loyalty and sincere efforts. Period upto 50 years is full of trials. Period between 18 to 26 may see financial troubles or mental diseases. Period from 27 to 50 years offers some stability. Female natives are capable, dignified and self-sufficient. Female natives have capacity to become wealthy through independent efforts. They can pursue a successful career in business and service. They achieve top rank through their own efforts at their employment place.</p>\r\n<p>Family Life: Natives have limited or no relationship with parents and siblings. While they are appreciated for bringing financial and social stability inspite of &nbsp;troubles they are often resented for their temper, intolerance and criticism of others. Married life is harmonious but separation maybe possible due to unforeseen circumstances. Partner is likely to have a demanding nature.</p>\r\n<p>Positives: Bread Winner for family, Self Made Individuals</p>\r\n<p>Negatives: Anger and Ego, Control Freaks, Restless</p>\r\n<p>Health: Cough and Cold</p>\r\n<p>Remedies: Jyestha natives are advised to pray to Lord Vishnu due to the Mangal-Budh relationship and also perform the ''Moola Shanti'' pooja for the Gandmoola Dosha.&nbsp;</p>', 1, '', 0, 1, '{"show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_layout":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 0, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 899, '', '2014-02-02 02:35:20', 899, '2014-03-06 12:06:32', '*', '2014-02-02 02:35:20', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 51, 181, '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', 0, 5, 9, 'jyestha nakshatra, 27 nakshatras, nakshatras ruled by mercury', 'jyestha nakshatra in vedic astrology', 13, '', 1),
(64, 'com_content.article', 'Mula', 'mula', '<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Mula Nakshatra is the ninteenth nakshatra among the <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=category&amp;id=12&amp;Itemid=112">27 Nakshatras</a> in Vedic Astrology. Mula means root in Sanskrit. The planetary lord of Mula Nakshatra is <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=9:ketu&amp;catid=9:9-planets&amp;Itemid=109">Ketu</a>. All the 4 Padas of Mula are in <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=30:dhana&amp;catid=11:12-signs&amp;Itemid=111">Dhana Rashi </a>while the symbol for Mula are a bunch of roots tied together. The gana is Rakshasha and the presiding deity is Nirriti who is the goddess of destruction. It falls under the category of Gand Moola Nakshatra. Vedic Astrology advises people not to take loans or grants when <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=2:chandra&amp;catid=9:9-planets&amp;Itemid=109">Chandra</a> is in Mula Nakshatra as they would be unable to pay the debt back.</p>\r\n<p>Physical Features: Natives have good physical features with bright eyes and beautiful limbs.</p>\r\n<p>Character &amp; Events: Female natives derive little happiness due to their proud and stubborn nature. Male natives are shrewd and capable. Mula Natives both male and female are good at handling adverse situations and guiding people through difficult times. Through tact and diplomacy Mula natives solve difficult scenarios. Having said that they often quit tasks halfway by influence of Mula ruler Ketu (planet which brings detachment). Mula natives are peace loving with an attractive personality and fixed set of principles. Inspite of numerous adversities they remain optimistic and achieve success in the desired field. On the downside they often overlook adversities and do not plan ahead in life. Due to this peculiar tendency they often invite debt and problems in life. There is no stability in career and there are constant changes of profession. Mula natives are advised to pursue a career where quitting or taking a break is possible. They are good orators and can make a good politician who talks the talk but rarely walks the walk. They can even make a career as financial or religious advisers, fine &nbsp;arts, writers, public speakers, doctors, healers, social work or philosophers.</p>\r\n<p>Family Life: Natives generally derive very little benefits through parents. They live a detached life and do not get too close to friends or family. They often have problems with drugs and alcohol addiction. For females marriage may result in unhappiness and even death of husband in some cases. Can have multiple love affairs and troubles through them. for males married life is satisfactory and spouse has all the adequate qualities.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Health: Problems with addictions, dangerous burns, violent accidents and broken bones are all possible.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Positives: Good Orators, Spiritual, Adventurous, Brave when Facing Adversities.</p>\r\n<p>Negatives: Uncaring, Self-destructive, No Planning.</p>\r\n<p>Remedies: Mula natives should pray to Ganesha or&nbsp;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dattatreya" target="_blank">Dattatreya</a></p>', 1, '', 0, 1, '{"show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_layout":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 0, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 899, '', '2014-02-02 02:39:19', 899, '2014-03-06 12:08:22', '*', '2014-02-02 02:39:19', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 52, 183, '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', 0, 3, 8, '27 nakshatras, mula nakshatra, ganda moola nakshatra, gandmool nakshatra, nakshatra ruled by ketu', 'mula nakshatra in vedic astrology', 13, '', 1),
(65, 'com_content.article', 'Purva Asadha', 'purva-asadha', '<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Purva Asadha is the tweentieth nakshatra among the <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=category&amp;id=12&amp;Itemid=112">27 Nakshtaras</a> in Vedic Astrology. The diety for this nakshatra is <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ap_(water)" target="_blank">Apas</a> while the gana is Manushya. The ruling planet for Purva Asadha is <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=6:shukra&amp;catid=9:9-planets&amp;Itemid=109">Shukra</a> and all the 4 Padas are located in <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=30:dhana&amp;catid=11:12-signs&amp;Itemid=111">Dhana Rashi</a>. The symbol is a hand fan. Purva Asadha is considered an auspicious nakshatra for female natives but inauspicious for male natives. Honesty is a trait which is best associated with this naksthatra.</p>\r\n<p>Physical Features: Natives have a lean and tall body with beautiful teeth, long ears and arms and narrow waist. Females have a beautiful face, attractive eyes and small lips. They have brown and curly hair and small feet. Female natives are known to put on weight in later years of life.</p>\r\n<p>Character &amp; Events: Purva Asadha natives are known for their honesty. But they have a tendency to jump to conclusions inspite of good intelligence. While they have good argumentative and convincing skills they are too rash in taking actions without proper thought and end up losing. Inspite of loss they are too adamant to accept fault. While they love giving out free advice they resent being advised by others. While outwardly they show to be courageous the inner reality and emotions are quite different. They tend to derive benefits from total strangers. Male natives have low character trait with minimum education and material assets. They may have a harsh and dominating personality but often have to work as underlings. Male natives possess very little administrative skills and can be quite quarrelsome. In a stark contrast female natives have a positive character. They are likely to think over actions before implementing them. They are successful in occupations which allow them to utilize their natural abilities. Period upto 32 years is full of trials. Period between 32 to 50 years suggests progress. As natives have a habit of helping without any expectations of returns career as doctor is highly recommended. Besides that they can work as antique collectors, in fine arts, as poets among other professions.</p>\r\n<p>Family Life: Natives enjoy a healthy relationship with parents and siblings and also derive benefits from them. There are chances to settle abroad if the native desires. Though marriage is delayed, it maybe happy to an extent. Children are talented and respectful. Children also increase the name and fame of the family.</p>\r\n<p>Health: Natives may suffer from an incurable disease. Also there can be breathing troubles, bronchitis, etc. Thigh problems and lung disorders like rheumatism possible.</p>\r\n<p>Positives: Artistic, Good looking, Influential</p>\r\n<p>Negatives: Stubborn, Inflexible, Egoistic.</p>\r\n<p>Remedies: Prayers to a calm goddess deity like Laxmi, Parvati, Saraswati or Mother Mary.&nbsp;</p>', 1, '', 0, 1, '{"show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_layout":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 0, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 899, '', '2014-02-02 02:40:04', 899, '2014-03-06 12:10:12', '*', '2014-02-02 02:40:04', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 53, 185, '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', 0, 3, 7, 'purva asadha nakshatra, nakshatra ruled by shukra, nakshatra ruled by venus, 27 nakshatras', 'purva asadha nakshatra in vedic astrology', 13, '', 1),
(66, 'com_content.article', 'Uttara Asadha', 'uttara-asadha', '<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Uttara Asadha is the twenty first nakshatra among the <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=category&amp;id=12&amp;Itemid=112">27 Nakshatras</a> of Vedic Astrology. While the first pada is in <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=30:dhana&amp;catid=11:12-signs&amp;Itemid=111">Dhana Rashi</a> the rest of the 3 Padas are in <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=31:makara&amp;catid=11:12-signs&amp;Itemid=111">Makara Rashi</a>. The planetary lord is <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=1:surya&amp;catid=9:9-planets&amp;Itemid=109">Surya</a> for Uttara Asadha while the gana is Devta. Symbol is an elephants tusk.</p>\r\n<p>Physical Features: Uttara Asadha natives have a well-proportioned body with broad head, long nose and bright eyes. They have a charming and graceful appearance in addition to somewhat fairer complexion.</p>\r\n<p>Character &amp; Events: Natives have a humanitarian vision to see all races as equal. Natives like to dress simple, respect everyone and are God fearing. They are secretive from others and unable to put full confidence in others. They are prone to flattery. They are forced with many responsibilities at a young age which shapes their character and gives them strength to work under pressure. Uttara Asadha natives have no qualms in accepting their fault or admitting to a mistake. Generally think over before taking a task which avoids them failures and resentment afterwards. They are recognized by society and honest in their business dealings. Female natives have a contented nature and can make a good administrator. They are keen to pursue social causes and events. Male natives have a good, honest and sincere character. They are peace loving, intelligent and wise. They believe in the philosophy of living and letting others live. Career in Politics, Entertainments, Counseling, Research, Wrestling, Painting and Army are possible among others.</p>\r\n<p>Family Life: Females are extremely devoted to their husbands. Natives both male and female are liked by everyone who comes in their contact. They are good and steady friends who help their friends in times of need. Married life is good and a good partner is indicated. Spouse is liable to health concerns especially gastric problems like acidity. Not much happiness through children and children can be a cause of concern for the native.</p>\r\n<p>Health: Native is prone to stomach problems, pulmonary diseases. In addition poor eyesight or some defect in the eyes also possible.</p>\r\n<p>Positives: Devoted to friends, Tolerant, Intelligent.</p>\r\n<p>Negatives: Health, Unable to Trust others.</p>\r\n<p>Remedies: Praying to Surya or Lord Vishnu.&nbsp;</p>', 1, '', 0, 1, '{"show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_layout":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 0, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 899, '', '2014-02-02 02:41:05', 899, '2014-03-06 12:11:35', '*', '2014-02-02 02:41:05', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 54, 187, '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', 0, 4, 6, '', 'uttara asadha nakshatra, nakshatra ruled by surya, nakshatra ruled by sun, 27 nakshatras,', 13, '', 1),
(67, 'com_content.article', 'Sravana', 'sravana', '<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Shravana (sometimes called sravana) is the twenty second nakshatra among the <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=category&amp;id=12&amp;Itemid=112">27 Nakshatras</a> in Vedic Astrology. The ruling planet is <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=2:chandra&amp;catid=9:9-planets&amp;Itemid=109">Chandra</a> for Sharavana and all the 4 Padas are located in <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=31:makara&amp;catid=11:12-signs&amp;Itemid=111">Makara Rashi</a> which is rashi of <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=7:shani&amp;catid=9:9-planets&amp;Itemid=109">Shani</a>. The gana is Devta and the symbol is three footprints. Shravana means ''To Listen'' in Sanskrit and true to its meaning the natives are great listeners and lend an ear to the needy and troubled. Goddess Saraswati is said to be born in this nakshatra.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Physical Appearance: Shravana natives have very attractive physical appearance. They have an attractive smile. Their height tends to be short and a peculiar mark is observed on the face like a mole or disfigurement. Sometimes the mark is on the shoulders. They have a gentle speech and maintain decorum under any circumstances.</p>\r\n<p>Character &amp; Events: Shravana natives have a set principle in life. They are driven by Shani''s discipline and Chandra''s emotions. They like cleanliness and do not like untidy people. Natives are God fearing and respect their elders. They live an honest life and favor victory of honesty. Natives are very helpful to others but they themselves are bereft of any help from others. In some cases the natives may be deceived by others in return for their help and kindness. As they live an honest life and do not like to harm others for personal gain only moderate success is possible. But on the bright side natives rarely see extreme harsh circumstances.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Female natives are kind and benevolent and have a very strong character with a calm appearance and personality. They have a gift to imbue courage in others. Males also share similar kind and helpful nature. Good education is suggested with scholarships, reputed degree and knowledge all endowed in individual. Period upto 30 years sees changes in life. Period between 30 to 45 years of life offers some stability. Period after 65 years shows remarkable progress both social and economical. Ideal career in Politics due to tact, diplomacy and kind nature. Besides that career in mechanical, technical work, petroleum or oil products is favorable. Natives can be successful in both business and service.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Family Life: Natives are fond of parents and genuinely cares for their parents. A great marriage is indicated with all the good qualities endowed in the partner. Natives are prone to extra-marital affairs.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Health: Any association of Chandra (lord of Shravana) + Shani (lord of Makara Rashi) is bound to create health complications. Natives may suffer from ear problems, skin diseases, eczema, rheumatism, tuberculosis and indigestion.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Positives: Kindness, Charitable, Ethical, Discipline, Modest</p>\r\n<p>Negatives: Creates Debt (due to kind nature), Hypersensitive, Health Issues</p>\r\n<p>Remedies: Prayers to Lord Vishnu and Goddess Saraswati are suggested for the natives.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, '', 0, 1, '{"show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_layout":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 0, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 899, '', '2014-02-02 02:41:33', 899, '2014-03-06 12:12:43', '*', '2014-02-02 02:41:33', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 55, 189, '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', 0, 3, 5, 'sravana nakshatra, 27 nakshatra, nakshatra ruled by chandra, nakshatra ruled by moon', 'sravana nakshatra in vedic astrology', 13, '', 1),
(68, 'com_content.article', 'Dhanistha', 'dhanistha', '<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Dhanistha Nakshatra is the twenty third nakshatra among the <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=category&amp;id=12&amp;Itemid=112">27 Nakshatras</a> in Vedic Astrology. The gana for dhanistha is Rakshasha while the symbol is a drum. First 2 Padas are located in <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=31:makara&amp;catid=11:12-signs&amp;Itemid=111">Makara Rashi</a> while the remaining 2 Padas are located in <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=32:kumbha&amp;catid=11:12-signs&amp;Itemid=111">Kumbha Rashi</a>. Dhanistha is ruled by <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=3:mangal&amp;catid=9:9-planets&amp;Itemid=109">Mangala</a> and located in the rashi of <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=7:shani&amp;catid=9:9-planets&amp;Itemid=109">Shani</a> (both Makara &amp; Kumbha are ruled by Shani). Like all Mangal-Shani relationship the native of Dhanistha has a passive-aggressive personality.</p>\r\n<p>Physical Features: Normally natives have a lean and tall body. In some cases short stature has also been observed. Native maybe pale if Mangal placement in horoscope is bad. Females like to dress well and wear colorful clothes.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Character &amp; Events: Natives are energetic and achieve their goals through activeness and dedication. They are blessed with wit and knowledge and act quickly. They have very high ambitions. They generally do not like causing troubles to others but once angered they are in no mood to forgive and forget the person who cause them anguish. They can wait for ages to get even with their enemies. They normally do not like disagreements and avoid them but if differences prop up they can be quite aggressive and even violent in some cases. Progress for them is observed after 24 years of life.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Natives born with Chandra in Kumbha Rashi can become quite good scientist, historians and researchers. Even career as a detective, spy or secretary to a high ranking official is possible. Caution in advised when going into business partnership. Generally better careers are indicated in service roles. Other careers include musicians, engineering, surgeons, doctors, mining among others.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Family Life: Natives get on well with brothers and sisters. But relatives can cause a lot of embarrassment and problems. Partner has good qualities but not much help from in-laws is possible. There is improvement in finances post marriage. But marriage is generally late and in worst case scenarios no marriage has also been seen.</p>\r\n<p>Health: Not good for health and afflicted with many diseases. Prone to cough, anemia etc. Though no prolonged illness is suggested.</p>\r\n<p>Positives: Insightful and Ambitious</p>\r\n<p>Negatives: Revengeful when Angered, Inconsiderate.</p>\r\n<p>Remedies: To the calm the aggression and hatred prayers to Lord Krishna and Lord Shiva are suggested.</p>', 1, '', 0, 1, '{"show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_layout":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 0, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 899, '', '2014-02-02 02:43:11', 899, '2014-03-06 12:14:39', '*', '2014-02-02 02:43:11', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 56, 191, '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', 0, 4, 4, 'dhanistha nakshatra, 27 nakshatras, nakshatra ruled by mangal, nakshatra ruled by mars', 'dhanistha nakshatra in vedic astrology', 13, '', 1),
(69, 'com_content.article', 'Shatabhisa', 'shatabhisa', '<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Shatabisha is the twenty fourth nakshatra among the <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=category&amp;id=12&amp;Itemid=112">27 Nakshatras</a> in Vedic Astrology. All the 4 Padas of Satabisha are located in <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=32:kumbha&amp;catid=11:12-signs&amp;Itemid=111">Kumbha Rashi</a> while the gana is Rakshasha. The presiding diety is Varuna and the symbol for Shatabisha is a circle. The nakshatra itself is ruled by <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=8:rahu&amp;catid=9:9-planets&amp;Itemid=109">Rahu</a>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Physical Features: Shatabisha natives have a soft body, wide head, attractive eyes and prominent nose. Male natives tend to be obese while female natives maybe lean and tall while also being fairly beautiful and elegant in disposition.</p>\r\n<p>Character &amp; Events: Shatabisha natives are a mixture of <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=7:shani&amp;catid=9:9-planets&amp;Itemid=109">Shani''s</a> seriousness and sudden outburst of Rahu. Natives are honest and truthful but prone to anger. Their anger easily subsides after sometime. They are adamant in their views and lead a lonesome life in solitude. Due to unpredictability of Rahu the native may at times be talkative while other times they may become depressive. They are quite intelligent and efficient but can be good or bad depending on mood on a particular day. They are quite shy in approach and do not like pomp or show. Their hidden talents are often discovered over a conversation with strangers.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Period up to 32 years of life is trialsome. Period after 32 years sees constant progress. Education is good and native is ideally a scientist, researcher or doctor who invents new medicines and operating procedures. Female natives are controlled in emotions and not easily angered. Female natives generally maintain a good and respectable position in the community. Males are quiet and thoughtful but prone to sudden anger outburst. They live in solitude and do not care for small talk.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Career in research, astrology, healing arts, astrology, astronomy, doctors and medicines is suggested among others.</p>\r\n<p>Family Life: A lot of troubles indicated through family members especially brothers. Native may not derive much benefit through father but mother provides love and affection for the native. Not ideal for a happy marital life even though spouse is good. Illicit relationship possible but they remain hidden from eyes of society.</p>\r\n<p>Health: Shatabhisha natives are prone to urinary diseases, breathing troubles and diabetes. May also contact sexually transmitted diseases if native is a sex addict. Problems due to cold weather and problems of jaw possible.</p>\r\n<p>Positives: Truthful, Perceptive and Emotionally Controlled</p>\r\n<p>Negatives: Lonesome, Depressive and Lack of Self Confidence</p>\r\n<p>Remedies: Prayers to Lord Shiva help with matters of Rahu, Shani and Chandra.&nbsp;</p>', 1, '', 0, 1, '{"show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_layout":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 0, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 899, '', '2014-02-02 02:44:09', 899, '2014-03-06 12:15:53', '*', '2014-02-02 02:44:09', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 57, 193, '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', 0, 4, 3, 'shatabhisa nakshatra, 27 nakshatras, nakshatra ruled by rahu', 'shatabhisa nakshatra in vedic astrology', 13, '', 1),
(70, 'com_content.article', 'Purva Bhadrapada', 'purva-bhadrapada', '<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Purva Bhadrapada is the twenty fifth nakshatra among the <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=category&amp;id=12&amp;Itemid=112">27 Nakshatras</a> in Vedic Astrology. The diety is Ajopada who is one of the Rudras. The first 3 Padas are in <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=32:kumbha&amp;catid=11:12-signs&amp;Itemid=111">Kumba Rashi</a> while the last pada is in <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=33:meena&amp;catid=11:12-signs&amp;Itemid=111">Meena Rashi</a>. Symbol for Purva Bhadrapada is a double faced man. The gana is Manushya and planetary lord is <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=5:guru&amp;catid=9:9-planets&amp;Itemid=109">Guru</a> for Purva Bhadrapada. Natives born with <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=2:chandra&amp;catid=9:9-planets&amp;Itemid=109">Chandra</a> in Meena Rashi are observed to have better results as compared to natives born with Chandra in Kumba Rashi for Purva Bhadrapada.</p>\r\n<p>Physical Features: Natives are generally medium sized with broad cheeck and flashy lips. They are peaceful but prone to occasional anger outburst. Natives born in Kumba Rashi are taller and leaner then those born in Meena Rashi.</p>\r\n<p>Character &amp; Events: Purva Bhadrapada natives live a simplistic lifestyle and dress quite simple. They are peaceful and have high principles in life. They are serious and mentally quite tensed. Due to their high principles they are bound to suffer mentally through wrong doers. Even small confrontation can be taken too personally by natives. Natives are fond of eating and rather eat unscrupulously. They provide an impartial view on any matter. They are ready to help others with no expectation in return. Financial status does not become a hindrance for them in getting respect and confidence of others. Native gets moderate success in financial dealing and money matters. They are quite miser in spending money. Natives are religious but do not like following age old customs and traditions.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Female natives are influential in the community and like cultural activities. Male natives are nervous in temperament and have a weak constitution. They are very serious in demeanor and talk. Purva Bhadrapada natives can be successful in both business and service roles. However ideal career is suggested in a government organization where unexpected promotions and gains are possible. Besides that career in banking, revenue collection department, teaching, acting, writering, research and astrology is possible among others. Period between 24 to 33 years sees remarkable progress. Period between 40 to 54 years would be golden period in life.</p>\r\n<p>Family Life: Native doesn''t get proper care and affection from mother who most likely works at an office. However the father provides love and undivided attention to the native. There are many qualities in father which a native can be proud of. However some disagreements are bound to crop up with father. Female natives are attached to their partners and blessed with good children. Female natives are wealthy or marry into a wealthy family.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Health: Natives suffer from Acidity, Diabetes and even Paralytic Attack. Problem with ribs and soles of feet possible.</p>\r\n<p>Positives: Good Logical Skills, Impartial View, Self Reliant</p>\r\n<p>Negatives: Tensed Nature. Serious, Miser in Spending</p>\r\n<p>Remedies: When tensed prayers to Lord Shiva are ideal. Also <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dattatreya">Dattatreye</a> puja is ideal.&nbsp;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dattatreya"><br /></a></p>', 1, '', 0, 1, '{"show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_layout":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 0, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 899, '', '2014-02-02 02:45:27', 899, '2014-03-06 12:18:12', '*', '2014-02-02 02:45:27', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 58, 195, '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', 0, 3, 2, 'purva bhadrapada nakshatra, purvabhadrapada nakshatra, 27 nakshatras, nakshatra ruled by guru, nakshatra ruled by jupiter', 'purva bhadrapada in vedic astrology', 13, '', 1);
