(94, 'com_content.article', 'Prarabdha', 'prarabdha', '<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;In Vedic Astrology there are concepts of Prarabdha and Purushartha. Prarabdha in English means Fate.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;The Prarabdha of an individual plays a big part in shaping his life. If an individual is meant to rise from Rags to Riches then Prarabdha pushes him in that direction. If he is meant to fall down from a top position in life then Prarabdha pushes him in that direction. It all depends on karma of an individual or in other words Purushartha. To a believer of Prarabdha, fate controls the destiny while for a believer of Purushartha, hard work controls the destiny. Actually the reality is somewhere in the middle.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Prarabdha and Purushartha are not on collision course but rather run parallel and meet at some point of the road. The Purushartha of today becomes the Prarabdha of tomorrow. The Prarabdha faced today maybe a result of Purshartha of yesterday. Similarly today''s Prarabdha may decide the Purushartha for tomorrow. In astrological terms the placement and aspect of benefic planets like Guru, Shukra and Chandra drive the good Prarabdha while placement and aspect of malefic planets like Shani, Mangal, Rahu and Ketu suggest bad Prarabdha which befalls a native. But there is the quintessential question as to where should one apply Prarabdha and where should one apply Purushartha. Vedic Astrology and ancient Vedic Text suggests leaving matters of Artha Houses (2nd house, 6th house and 10th house) and Kama Houses (3rd house, 7th house and 11th house) to Prarabdha. Well to be more accurate leave matters of Savings, Popularity in Media, Matters of Debt, Marriage, Business Partnership (success or failure in partnership), Career Standing, Financial Gains and Quality and Quantity of Friends to Prarabdha. Not every matter in the concerned houses is better to leave to Prarabdha but knowing that Artha Houses and Kama Houses are driven by Prarabdha saves pain in future as they are beyond one''s control.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;As Kabir rightly said in his doha:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>Manushya kadi balwaan nahi; Samaya sab se balwaan<br />Kaabe Arjuna lutiyo; Wahi dhanush wahi baan</h4>\r\n<p>Translation: Time is far more powerful compared to the human. The greatest of the warrior Arjuna lost to a bunch of tribesman of forest even though he was using the same quiver and arrows which he used to defeat mighty warriors.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Countless stories exist to justify Saint Kabir''s views. But the point put across is not to get arrogant or conceited if you find victory and not to get deflated and lose hope at loss. Accept your Prarabdha and work towards your Purushartha.&nbsp;</p>', 1, '', 0, 1, '{"show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_layout":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 0, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 899, '', '2014-03-25 12:35:27', 0, '2014-03-25 11:37:10', '*', '2014-03-25 11:35:50', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 87, 280, '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', 0, 3, 0, 'vedic astrology, fate in astrology, prarabdha in astrology, learn vedic astrology, vedic astrology tutorials', 'prarabdha in astrology', 19, '', 1),
(95, 'com_content.article', 'Purushartha', 'purushartha', '<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;In Vedic Astrology the term Purushartha means Karma or doing your duty (not just any work). It is the driving force and the foremost reason why astrology gets it wrong in terms of forecasting future of the native. Just like there are Variants, Pie Values, Friction and Worst Case Scenarios in Mathematics, Science and Programming which cause calculations to go awry there is Purushartha in astrology which puts all the calculations as meaningless and native achieves things which cannot be calculated at birth. This single word maligns astrology like no other one does yet this article is only meant to praise this nemesis called Purushartha cause it is truly a great nemesis.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Purushartha is nothing but hard work without any sort of expectations in return. The very essence of Bhagvad Gita can summarize Purushartha like no one else can:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;"One cannot achieve anything without doing Karma (Purushartha). Don''t try to get anything for free. No work is bereft of gains. One should not ever get depressed in life. One should not lose confidence while doing his Karma (Purushartha)." -- Pandurang Athvale</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Purushartha and <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=81:prarabdha&amp;catid=41:main-articles">Prarabdha</a> are not on collision course but run parellel and intersect at some point of the long road. So people who loathe fate and luck should not get agitated at those who believe in it and those who believe in fate and luck should understand that today''s hard work is tomorrow''s good luck. Some people are born with the knowledge of what Purushartha he needs to pursue to be successful in life. Generally they are the people who taunt everyone else with early success. What they fail to realize is that Prarabdha was responsible for making them pursue the respected field and gain success. By taunting others today''s bad karma would become bad Prarabdha for tomorrow and hit them hard on the face.&nbsp;In similar manner people who believe too much in luck and fate refuse to get out of their cocoon and work hard towards a fixed objective. What they fail to realize is today''s Purushartha would result in good karma and ultimately good Prarabdha in the future.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;There is a dilemma in people when it comes to using Purushartha or &nbsp;applying Prarabdha. Vedic Astrology and Vedic Texts suggest trying hard (Purushartha) for matters of Dharma Houses (<a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=10:tanu-bhava&amp;catid=10:12-houses&amp;Itemid=114">1st house</a>, <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=14:putra-bhava&amp;catid=10:12-houses&amp;Itemid=110">5th house</a> and <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=18:bhagya-sthana&amp;catid=10:12-houses&amp;Itemid=110">9th house</a>) as well as Moksha Houses (<a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=13:matru-bhava&amp;catid=10:12-houses&amp;Itemid=110">4th house</a>, <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=17:mrityu-sthana&amp;catid=10:12-houses&amp;Itemid=110">8th house</a> and <a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=21:vyaya-bhava&amp;catid=10:12-houses&amp;Itemid=110">12th house</a>). To be more precise one should try hard for a good character, good health, good education, being religious as well try hard to get peace and happiness, think of death and rebirths and also work towards minimizing losses as well as gaining liberation from cycle of life and death by attaining Moksha.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Astrologers are generally not sought until situation is worse and all hope is lost. Some people are highly negative and consult astrologers to find out the right time to eat and sleep. What I personally advise is to learn about your Purushartha or goal of your life from astrologers as nothing is wrong in that. After that only visit him in times of calamity for solutions if possible through astrology. An honest astrologer is sure to give you right advise about the right course of action to take.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Finally don''t lose hope when all is lost and don''t get over the moon when you gain everything you''ve set out to do. Both are temperory. Your actions are permanent. So stick to your Purushartha and learn to enjoy the Prarabdha which has befallen you whether it is good or bad.&nbsp;</p>', 1, '', 0, 1, '{"show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_layout":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 0, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 899, '', '2014-03-25 12:38:56', 899, '2014-03-25 11:40:22', '*', '2014-03-25 11:39:45', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 88, 282, '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', 0, 3, 0, 'purushartha, hard work in astrology, learn vedic astrology, vedic astrology tutorials', 'purushartha in vedic astrology', 19, '', 1);
