(474, 84, 1, '', '2014-03-25 11:24:12', 899, 3886, 'df90fe1a28c68ed973289cb182e00853107b88a0', '{"id":84,"asset_id":273,"title":"Gaja Kesari Yoga","alias":"gky","introtext":"<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Gaja Kesari Yoga (GKY) is formed when the noble <a title=\\"Guru Article Link\\" href=\\"index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=5:guru&amp;catid=9:9-planets&amp;Itemid=109\\">Guru<\\/a> occupies Vishnu Sthanas from <a title=\\"Chandra Article Link\\" href=\\"index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=2:chandra&amp;catid=9:9-planets&amp;Itemid=109\\">Chandra<\\/a> or Ascendant. Gaj means an elephant in sanskrit while Kesari means a lion. There are different interpretations of the meaning of this yoga but what has been observed is the native with such yoga is influential and formidable but at the same time calm, composed, learned and humble with others. In simpler terms he is courageous like a lion but smart and peaceful like an elephant.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Guru in <a title=\\"Vishnu Sthanas Link\\" href=\\"index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=72:kendra-stahanas&amp;catid=41:main-articles\\">Vishnu Sthanas<\\/a> from Lagna or Chandra is not a big deal. It could happen in a lot of horoscopes. Yet not all of them get the benefits of GKY. What is important is Guru is in kendra in a favorable rashi and not aspected by malefic planets. That happens quit rarely. The best type of GKY is formed when Guru+Chandra are together in Vishnu Sthanas from ascendant and located in Karka Rashi or Meena Rashi. Even Dhana Rashi which belongs to Guru can lessen the effects as it has a fiery nature which doesn''t go well with Chandra who has watery nature. Auspicious placement of Guru+Chandra in a favorable rashi also gives rise to Laxmi Yoga. It is very likely that such natives enjoy full benefits of GKY. GKY doesn''t give expected results if Guru is in Makara Rashi, aspected by enemy planets or bereft of strength.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Simplest way to find if there is indeed a GKY is to look at the native himself. If he is rich and posseses all comforts from birth and by nature he is calm, good mannered, good cultured and religious then rest assured there is likely to be GKY or some sort of Guru+Chandra associations. This is one of the few yogas which gives results from inception and doesn''t need time to fructify.&nbsp;<\\/p>","fulltext":"","state":1,"catid":"14","created":"2014-03-25 12:23:25","created_by":"899","created_by_alias":"","modified":"2014-03-25 11:24:12","modified_by":"899","checked_out":"899","checked_out_time":"2014-03-25 11:23:26","publish_up":"2014-03-25 11:24:12","publish_down":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","images":"{\\"image_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"float_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_caption\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"float_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_caption\\":\\"\\"}","urls":"{\\"urla\\":false,\\"urlatext\\":\\"\\",\\"targeta\\":\\"\\",\\"urlb\\":false,\\"urlbtext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetb\\":\\"\\",\\"urlc\\":false,\\"urlctext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetc\\":\\"\\"}","attribs":"{\\"show_title\\":\\"\\",\\"link_titles\\":\\"\\",\\"show_tags\\":\\"\\",\\"show_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"info_block_position\\":\\"\\",\\"show_category\\":\\"\\",\\"link_category\\":\\"\\",\\"show_parent_category\\":\\"\\",\\"link_parent_category\\":\\"\\",\\"show_author\\":\\"\\",\\"link_author\\":\\"\\",\\"show_create_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_modify_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_publish_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_item_navigation\\":\\"\\",\\"show_icons\\":\\"\\",\\"show_print_icon\\":\\"\\",\\"show_email_icon\\":\\"\\",\\"show_vote\\":\\"\\",\\"show_hits\\":\\"\\",\\"show_noauth\\":\\"\\",\\"urls_position\\":\\"\\",\\"alternative_readmore\\":\\"\\",\\"article_layout\\":\\"\\",\\"show_publishing_options\\":\\"\\",\\"show_article_options\\":\\"\\",\\"show_urls_images_backend\\":\\"\\",\\"show_urls_images_frontend\\":\\"\\"}","version":2,"ordering":"0"