(476, 85, 1, '', '2014-03-25 11:29:19', 899, 3325, '04996c5d19dbfc124132ad31c9ab40d5eeca8a62', '{"id":85,"asset_id":275,"title":"Laxmi Sthanas","alias":"laxmi","introtext":"<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Laxmi Sthanas are the trine consisting of <a title=\\"1st house link\\" href=\\"index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=10:tanu-bhava&amp;catid=10:12-houses&amp;Itemid=114\\">1st house<\\/a>, <a title=\\"5th house link\\" href=\\"index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=14:putra-bhava&amp;catid=10:12-houses&amp;Itemid=110\\">5th house<\\/a> and <a title=\\"9th house link\\" href=\\"index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=18:bhagya-sthana&amp;catid=10:12-houses&amp;Itemid=110\\">9th house<\\/a>. They are also known as Trikon Sthana (Triangle Houses). Ironically all the 3 concerned houses rule Dharma. Goddess Laxmi is the wife of Lord Vishnu and goddess of wealth and prosperity. She is also the overseer of fortune and luck.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;There is a catch to the name Laxmi Sthanas. 1st house represents character and moral values, 5th house represents knowledge and wisdom and 9th house represents faith and religion. Those who have a good moral values, possess knowledge and wisdom as well as practice faith and religion are said to gain wealth and prosperity. All the 3 houses rule Dharma so in a way, it can be said that wealth and prosperity comes to those who practice Dharma.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;From an astrological perspective Laxmi Sthanas determine fame, fortune and luck. If the house lords of Laxmi Sthanas form Parivartana Yoga or located in Vishnu Sthanas then the concerned native is lucky and famous in life. If the house lords of Laxmi Sthanas are in dushamsthanas or debilitated then native maybe bereft of fame and fortune.&nbsp;<\\/p>","fulltext":"","state":1,"catid":"19","created":"2014-03-25 12:28:14","created_by":"899","created_by_alias":"","modified":"2014-03-25 11:29:19","modified_by"