(484, 87, 1, '', '2014-03-25 11:35:50', 899, 4417, '1ecfe6a34712324ea35cd76daf77e0964e4446fb', '{"id":87,"asset_id":279,"title":"Prarabdha","alias":"prarabdha","introtext":"<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;In Vedic Astrology there are concepts of Prarabdha and Purushartha. Prarabdha in English means Fate.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;The Prarabdha of an individual plays a big part in shaping his life. If an individual is meant to rise from Rags to Riches then Prarabdha pushes him in that direction. If he is meant to fall down from a top position in life then Prarabdha pushes him in that direction. It all depends on karma of an individual or in other words Purushartha. To a believer of Prarabdha, fate controls the destiny while for a believer of Purushartha, hard work controls the destiny. Actually the reality is somewhere in the middle.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Prarabdha and Purushartha are not on collision course but rather run parallel and meet at some point of the road. The Purushartha of today becomes the Prarabdha of tomorrow. The Prarabdha faced today maybe a result of Purshartha of yesterday. Similarly today''s Prarabdha may decide the Purushartha for tomorrow. In astrological terms the placement and aspect of benefic planets like Guru, Shukra and Chandra drive the good Prarabdha while placement and aspect of malefic planets like Shani, Mangal, Rahu and Ketu suggest bad Prarabdha which befalls a native. But there is the quintessential question as to where should one apply Prarabdha and where should one apply Purushartha. Vedic Astrology and ancient Vedic Text suggests leaving matters of Artha Houses (2nd house, 6th house and 10th house) and Kama Houses (3rd house, 7th house and 11th house) to Prarabdha. Well to be more accurate leave matters of Savings, Popularity in Media, Matters of Debt, Marriage, Business Partnership (success or failure in partnership), Career Standing, Financial Gains and Quality and Quantity of Friends to Prarabdha. Not every matter in the concerned houses is better to leave to Prarabdha but knowing that Artha Houses and Kama Houses are driven by Prarabdha saves pain in future as they are beyond one''s control.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;As Kabir rightly said in his doha:&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<h4>\\u201cManushya kadi balwaan nahi; Samaya sab se balwaan<br \\/>Kaabe Arjuna lutiyo; Wahi dhanush wahi baan\\u201d<\\/h4>\\r\\n<p>Translation: Time is far more powerful compared to the human. The greatest of the warrior Arjuna lost to a bunch of tribesman of forest even though he was using the same quiver and arrows which he used to defeat mighty warriors.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Countless stories exist to justify Saint Kabir''s views. But the point put across is not to get arrogant or conceited if you find victory and not to get deflated and lose hope at loss. Accept your Prarabdha and work towards your Purushartha.&nbsp;<\\/p>","fulltext":"","state":1,"catid":"19","created":"2014-03-25 12:35:27","created_by":"899","created_by_alias":"","modified":"2014-03-25 11:35:50","modified_by":"899","checked_out":"899","checked_out_time":"2014-03-25 11:35:27","publish_up":"2014-03-25 11:35:50","publish_down":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","images":"{\\"image_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"float_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_caption\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"float_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_caption\\":\\"\\"}","urls":"{\\"urla\\":false,\\"urlatext\\":\\"\\",\\"targeta\\":\\"\\",\\"urlb\\":false,\\"urlbtext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetb\\":\\"\\",\\"urlc\\":false,\\"urlctext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetc\\":\\"\\"}","attribs":"{\\"show_title\\":\\"\\",\\"link_titles\\":\\"\\",\\"show_tags\\":\\"\\",\\"show_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"info_block_position\\":\\"\\",\\"show_category\\":\\"\\",\\"link_category\\":\\"\\",\\"show_parent_category\\":\\"\\",\\"link_parent_category\\":\\"\\",\\"show_author\\":\\"\\",\\"link_author\\":\\"\\",\\"show_crea